Compiling
-------------------
Requires a C++17 compiler. No external dependencies.

Run
$ make

The compiled binary will be created in a new bin/ directory.

Usage
-------------------
$ ./3dc [OPTIONS] input_type input_file output_type output_file

Where input_type and output_type is one of:
"stl", "stlb", or "obj"

Transform Options
-------------------
Transforms are applied to the model geometry before encoding output.
Multiple transforms can be specified and are applied in the order given.

  -t, --translate X Y Z    Translate by (X, Y, Z)
  -rx, --rotate-x DEG      Rotate around X axis by DEG degrees
  -ry, --rotate-y DEG      Rotate around Y axis by DEG degrees
  -rz, --rotate-z DEG      Rotate around Z axis by DEG degrees
  -s, --scale FACTOR       Uniform scale by FACTOR

Examples:
  ./3dc -t 0 0 10 obj model.obj obj translated.obj    # Shift Z by 10
  ./3dc -rx 90 obj model.obj obj rotated.obj          # Rotate around X
  ./3dc -s 2 obj model.obj obj scaled.obj             # Double size
  ./3dc -s 0.5 -t 0 0 10 -rz 45 obj in.obj obj out.obj  # Chained transforms

OBJ Format Limitations
-------------------
All geometry is triangulated on output. N-gon faces are triangulated using
ear clipping during import.

The following OBJ features are not supported:
- Object names (o) and groups (g) are ignored
- Smoothing groups (s) are ignored
- Negative vertex indices not supported
- Line (l) and point (p) elements not supported
- Free-form geometry (curves, surfaces) not supported
- Texture map options in MTL files are ignored
- Per-vertex colors not supported
